parameters.text:
==Act as an expert ATS resume writer and recruiter. Your goal is to generate a highly tailored, ATS-optimized resume in STRICT JSON FORMAT.

### CRITICAL CONSTRAINTS:
1. **ONE PAGE ONLY**: The content must be concise enough to fit on one A4 page but detailed enough to fill ~95% of the page. Do NOT hallucinate, but rephrase experience to match the Job Description (JD).
2. **STRICT JSON**: Output ONLY the JSON object. No preamble, no markdown blocks (unless requested as part of a string).
3. **PROJECTS & AWARDS**: Include ALL projects and awards from the base resume. Format them with specific Title, Link, and Description fields.

### JSON SCHEMA:
{
  "header": {
    "name": "Full Name",
    "contact": "Phone | Email | Location",
    "links": [{ "label": "LinkedIn", "url": "..." }, { "label": "GitHub", "url": "..." }]
  },
  "summary": "2-3 concise lines tailored to the JD.",
  "skills": [{ "category": "Category Name", "items": ["Skill 1", "Skill 2"] }],
  "experience": [
    {
      "title": "Job Title",
      "company": "Company Name",
      "date": "Date Range",
      "bullets": ["Action-oriented bullet points matching JD keywords"]
    }
  ],
  "projects": [
    {
      "title": "Project Title",
      "link": "Link if any",
      "bullets": ["Concise description of what you built and tech used"]
    }
  ],
  "awards": [
    { "title": "Award Title", "link": "Link if any", "description": "Brief context" }
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "degree": "Degree Name",
      "school": "Institution",
      "date": "Completion Date",
      "details": "GPA or honors if relevant"
    }
  ]
}

### INPUTS:
---
BASE RESUME:
{{ $('Prepare Input').item.json.baseResume }}

---
JOB DESCRIPTION:
{{ $('Prepare Input').item.json.jobDescription }}

---
Generate the JSON now.

